description.4: While in astral form, Dr. Strange travels to the Far East to commune with the man known as the Aged Genghis!
description.8: Daredevil to the rescue! A cruise ship is under attack from a traveling “magician.”
description.9: After an armored, drunken rampage through Times Square, Tony is encouraged by his staff to take a personal leave from Stark International. With Iron Man out of commission, Colonel James Rhodes dons the suit, and title, of Iron Man.
description.12: Thor's worshippers are pitted against each other...thanks to the Crusader! Meanwhile, Thor makes a shocking revelation about his foe.
description.13: The alternate future of the Marvel Universe! The fate of Vision and Scarlet Witch! Daredevil and Black Widow- nearly 30 years after their first meeting! Plus, what if Sharon Carter had survived?
description.14: The Fantastic Four provide aid to some Negative Zone wanderers. A weakened Annihilus vows to destroy the entire universe- including his own!
description.15: As Kitty Pryde tries to make her way back onto the X-Men's roster, Wolverine prepares to do just the opposite. Meanwhile, the Summers men head off on a family-only trip and run into someone unexpected...
description.22: After a series of robberies at Osborn Manufacturing, a new foe musters their strength and gets equipped for serious mayhem. The Hobgoblin is here, and he fears no one!
description.23: After Hank Pym is exonerated of all crimes, he leaves the Avengers for a new civilian life. The Masters of Evil are finally behind bars, and the team can breathe a collective sigh of relief. A new dawn awaits the Avengers!
description.24: The murderous Scarecrow has targeted CUA members. In order to protect the remaining members Captain America joins their campaign!
description.25: Maggia criminal Hammerhead is finally going behind bars. What Power Man and Iron Fist thought would be an easy job soon proves difficult when Hammerhead’s schemes come into play!
description.26: The story behind Crystar! The making of the mighty Marvel handbook! And so much more in this nostalgic preview series from Marvel Comics past!
description.28: The Crazy mascot Obnoxio the Clown, along with unlikely allies the X-Men, takes on Eye Scream, who can turn himself into various forms of, well, ice cream.
description.31: Luke, Lando and Leia continue the hunt for Boba Fett, in order to rescue Han!
description.37: The INCREDIBLE HULK is on the run once again...but he never expected to run into not one, but TWO supervillains - the mutant menaces of BLOB and UNUS THE UNTOUCHABLE! Can even the Hulk win when he's outnumbered? Plus: Daredevil helps a child find his best friend in the vast urban jungle of New York City!
description.38: Dazzler fan Karl Fredericks gets a little too close (and a little too obsessed) with the singing mutant sensation. Will Alison see the truth before it’s too late?
description.39: Can Leia and C-3PO escape Imperial capture after the betrayal of the bounty hunter Dengar?
description.40: Hired for the same job, Power Man and Iron Fist are pitted against Vienna, a master spy! Will the Heroes for Hire be able to get their paycheck when Vienna seems to always be one-step ahead?
description.41: The First Appearance of Hobgoblin!  A shadowy figure shows an interest in obtaining Green Goblin's gear. Who can this figure be? And will Spider-Man be able to prevent the shadow of evil's past from clouding the sky?
description.42: Tony Stark creates a cerebral scanner that will determine Hank Pym's innocence. Jennifer Walters reverts back to She-Hulk after a heated argument with Hawkeye. Plus, the Avengers witness Hank Pym's single-handed victory over the Masters of Evil!
description.43: Steve Rogers and Bernie Rosenthal are on a date when they are suddenly interrupted by a mad Captain America! How can Captain America be fighting Steve Rogers when he is Steve Rogers? Which one is the real Steve Rogers?
description.50: Journalist Ben Urich is on the wrong side of the Kingpin! Thankfully, Daredevil is already on the trail.
description.51: Machine Man comes to Tony Stark seeking help. Stark, severely drunk, puts on his Iron Man and attacks Machine Man without asking questions first.
description.52: The Premiere Issue of the First Ongoing New Mutants series, celebrating the 40th Anniversary of the mutant team!  A new team of young mutants is initiated into Professor Xavier's School for Gifted Youngsters! Their first trial: the Danger Room!
description.53: Sick and destructive, Hrungnir is in Chicago- and is on a mission to kill Thor! Sif has a difficult adjustment to the Midgardian way of life.
description.54: Our heroes discover a primitive culture deep within the Negative Zone! At the Baxter Building, Alicia and Franklin have some unexpected company.
description.58: Following Clea’s departure, a crowd of hopeful mages knocks on Doctor Strange’s door to become his new disciple!
description.62: Daredevil plays a little game of Russian Roulette with a hospitalized Bullseye. Has DD finally gone too far in his quest for vengeance? Matt Murdock is a changed man, and not for the better.
description.63: Tony's staff is concerned about his recent erratic behavior and drinking habits. Tony is concerned about Indries, the new woman in his life. Will Iron Man be able to conquer his own personal demons?
description.65: Lady Sif decides to live on Earth with Thor! But what happens when Sif discovers Thor's "friend" Shawna Lynde? Could Donald Blake be in over his head?
description.66: The cat's out of the bag, as Magneto announces he is the father of Scarlet Witch and Quicksilver! Plus, Magneto meets his granddaughter Luna for the first time. The twins' secret history, and the identity of their mother, also revealed.
description.67: Beast and Thing have one thing in common- both heroes are rapidly devolving into a mutated state! Can Reed Richards save Grimm before he's lost to Virus X? And how will the X-Men handle a teammate gone rogue? Plus, Silver Surfer is robbed of the Power Cosmic...only to discover that his lover Shalla Bal is Galactus' new herald!
description.68: Reed has built a new portal to the Negative Zone, and Ben is not happy about it! Will the Negative Zone's potential outweigh its dangers? Meanwhile, Johnny finds himself in a love triangle with his actress friends!
description.69: The X-Men find themselves on a world transformed by the Brood.  Is there any way to save the planet, let alone themselves?
description.77: A down in the dumps Stilt-Man decides to get a confidence boost by besting Spider-Man in battle. After Stilt-Man makes improvements to his battlesuit, he finds and tangles with the web-slinger. Can Spider-Man defend himself? Or will he once again fall to the Stilt-Man's crushing might?
description.78: The Avengers, and the general public, anxiously await Hank Pym's trial. But with Egghead alive and vengeful, the Masters of Evil may interrupt the due process of law!
description.79: The battle with Baron Zemo continues when Captain America manages to rescue Arnie Roth, but just when they think the fight is over, Baron Zemo send his hordes of mutates after them? Will Captain America manage to escape Baron Zemo's clutches?
description.80: The search for Han Solo begins here! Can Luke and the others stop Boba Fett and get their captured friend back?
description.81: When former supervillain Unus the Untouchable shifts to petty crimes against small businesses, Power Man and Iron Fist are forced to take down his impenetrable force fields!
description.84: Rogue breaks and enters into Dazzler’s apartment for a second shot at victory, but the Heroes for Hire have gotten a heads up!
description.85: It’s Peter’s Fifth High School Reunion, and some past problems threaten to bubble to the surface! Plus, Spidey’s case against Kingpin hits a snag when key evidence incriminating Fisk is destroyed!
description.87: On Thor's birthday, the Norns look back on how the Thunder God came to be – through Odin's wishes for a son who would possess the power of both heaven and earth!
description.91: The Impossible Man unleashes his unique brand of chaos in the Marvel Office…and the X-Men are in fast pursuit! Plus, what’s become of Zabu, Ka-Zar's sabretooth tiger? Professor X and his band of mutants seek answers- and take names!
description.92: The Hand has revealed their plan to resurrect Elektra, and DD, Widow, Stick, and Stone must prevent this unnatural evil! Elektra lives again.
description.93: The Fantastic Four receive a desperate call for help from one of Johnny Storm's friends! It's Sharon Selleck, and she's trapped in a nightmare in a rural New York town named King's Crossing! What could be happening in this quaint little dairy village? The FF invade incognito to investigate! And when the foursome recalls their previous trip to King's Crossing in Fantastic Four 2, a sobering reality hits them! Could the three skrulls that were turned into cows ages ago...somehow still be haunting this town and its simple residents? Therein lies the mystery! An excellent story!
description.94: Following the fall-out with the Chessmen, Tony retreats to a pub with Indries. Rhodey is still recovering from a venomous spider-bite that leaves him incapacitated. On his return to Stark International, Tony feels the urge to drink mass amounts of whiskey.
description.95: Can Thor and the Asgardians save Earth from the crushing might of Tyr and Loki? Loki uncovers the truth about Odin's relationship with Queen Jolena.
description.96: It's a family reunion Vision won't forget, as he and Wonder Man are attacked by Grim Reaper! Eric Williams is the Grim Reaper, notorious villain and brother to Simon Williams, Wonder Man. Vision's connection to the Williams' brother is brought to the surface, as Scarlet Witch scrambles to save her husband!
description.97: The team is aided by allies Spider-Man, Captain America, and the X-Men to battle Gladiator, a ferocious Shi'ar warrior!
description.98: As their ship is falling apart, Storm begins to transform into a Brood.  It's terror in space as the X-Men try to return home.

3.text: Street merchants take on a young gang to claim their turf in Brooklyn. And Moon Knight is smack dab in the middle.

4.text: While in astral form, Dr. Strange travels to the Far East to commune with the man known as the Aged Genghis!

5.text: Daimon Hellstrom has won the game of life by cutting ties from his satanic bloodline, but can he truly break off with his darker half so quickly?

7.text: It’s a warm family welcome when She-Hulk assures her cousin Bruce that she is happy as the Green Giantess. Later, the Avengers Mansion is attacked by the Leader!

10.text: A mysterious saboteur turns the Danger Room against Psyche!  But the rest of the New Mutants may have it worse when they encounter the Sentinels!
A mysterious saboteur turns the Danger Room against Psyche!  But the rest of the New Mutants may have it worse when they encounter the Sentinels!

16.text: Doctor Octopus descends on a recuperating Black Cat! Spider-Man is able to fight him off, but on his way home he runs afoul of the Gladiator in a case of mistaken identity, and throws down with the longtime Daredevil villain.

17.text: Moon Knight mounts a rescue mission against the satanic cult that is holding Jack Russell hostage.

18.text: Expecting to reunite with his mother, Shang-Chi returns to New York but encounters assassins everywhere he turns.

21.text: Killraven: Warrior of the Worlds.  Killraven leads the Freemen against  Martian invaders while searching for his lost brother Joshua!  The War for Earth's freedom continues!

25.text: While transporting Maggia criminal Hammerhead to prison, Power Man and Iron Fist soon realize they’ve been framed! Back in the city, Colleen Wing and Bob Hope take their sparring practice to the next level.

27.text: “Escape from New York!” The battle you never thought you’d see: Ka-Zar versus Spider-Man! But why are these allies playing for keeps?

28.text: The Crazy mascot Obnoxio the Clown, along with unlikely allies the X-Men, takes on Eye Scream, who can turn himself into various forms of, well, ice cream.

33.text: Hulk fights a long, fierce battle against the Humanoids when he refuses the Leader’s proposal to join him as a world leader.

34.text: Overmind, now under the control of six psychics, aims to change his ways…

40.text: Power Man and Iron Fist go head-to-head trying to capture the same bounty as Vienna!

44.text: Moon Knight tries to track down the Werewolf by Night before he is abducted by a satanic cult!

45.text: Reston's solo endeavor turns out to be a trap, forcing Shang and Leiko to go on a rescue mission.

52.text: A new team of young mutants is initiated into Professor Xavier's School for Gifted Youngsters! Their first trial: the Danger Room!
Bob McLeod delivers his version of the iconic charging team shot, masterfully introducing the teen team.

55.text: The New Mutants, The Starjammers, and the X-Men must band together to save a Brood-infected Professor X once the Brood begins to take hold? Can their mentor be saved or will he die by their hands?
The New Mutants, The Starjammers, and the X-Men must band together to save a Brood-infected Professor X once the Brood begins to take hold? Can their mentor be saved or will he die by their hands?

56.text: In the aftermath of the battle with Doc Ock, Black Cat finds herself severely wounded and in need of medical attention. While Felicia battles for her life, Spider-Man confesses his feelings for her.

57.text: The Savage Land is swept into Ramona’s destructive plot for A.I.M! Peter Parker tries to help Shanna through her grief.

58.text: Following Clea’s departure, a crowd of hopeful mages knocks on Doctor Strange’s door to become his new disciple!

59.text: Overmind casts visions into the mind of Doctor Strange. But is Overmind actually the one responsible?

61.text: Bruce’s date night with Bereet is interrupted by journalists and Leader's Humanoids!

70.text: Black Cat's luck has come through as Spider-Man finds her alive and well! Before the pair can figure out their own relationship, Doctor Octopus enters the picture! After a quick fracas, Doc Ock escapes with Felicia as his prisoner as well as a component for a bomb big enough to level the city. Can Spidey stop Doc Ock's insane gambit?

71.text: The miraculous resurrection of Ka-Zar! What strange, scientific forces have brought him back from the edge?

72.text: Shang-Chi races spies and secret agents to a secret codebook.

73.text: Celebrate Kitty Pryde's 14th birthday with the X-Men!

76.text: Marc and Marlene return to the birthplace of Moon Knight…the Sudanese desert. There, they must protect Lord Khonshu’s priceless relics from grave robbers!

81.text: Power Man and Iron Fist realize there’s more than one way to bring down Unus the Untouchable!

84.text: Rogue breaks and enters into Dazzler’s apartment for a second shot at victory, but the Heroes for Hire have gotten a heads up!

85.text: It’s Peter’s Fifth High School Reunion, and some past problems threaten to bubble to the surface! Plus, Spidey’s case against Kingpin hits a snag when key evidence incriminating Fisk is destroyed!

86.text: The Avengers are called before the Security Council of the UN, where the Fantastic Four are on trial for failing to inform the UN of the Inhumans’ existence. Now, the Avengers have been called in as a neutral party to investigate the situation. Will the Inhumans be marked by the UN as potential threats?

87.text: On Thor's birthday, the Norns look back on how the Thunder God came to be – through Odin's wishes for a son who would possess the power of both heaven and earth!

88.text: The Defenders have a final battle against a mind-controlled Squadron Supreme and the Overmind!

90.text: The Hulk is finally given a hero’s treatment!

91.text: The Impossible Man unleashes his unique brand of chaos in the Marvel Office…and the X-Men are in fast pursuit! Plus, what’s become of Zabu, Ka-Zar's sabretooth tiger? Professor X and his band of mutants seek answers- and take names!

99.text: When you have two criminal masterminds, that's a lot of egos to manage. The Owl and Doc Ock's union proves short-lived as the two criminals turn on each other when they suspect each other of holding out on stolen equipment. Meanwhile, Peter tries to lend a helping hand to his friend Debra Whitman.
